    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://simme.dev/projects/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2020 13:14:38 +0100</pubDate>
      <author>simme@arcticbit.se (Simon Aronsson)</author>
      <guid>https://simme.dev/projects/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Software development is not only my day job but also one of my biggest passions. Some of the software projects
I pour time into outside of work are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;


&lt;div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;
    simskij/awesome-software-architecture
  &lt;/h3&gt;
  
	&lt;p&gt;
	  A curated list of resources on software architecture and related practices. To quote the repository readme:
&amp;gt; Software architecture aims to describe the high level structures of software as well as the discipline of &amp;gt; creating them. As this topic is pretty broad, it might contain resources also present in more niche lists.
  &lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;a class=&#34;github-button&#34;
		 href=&#34;https://github.com/simskij/awesome-software-architecture&#34; 
      data-icon=&#34;octicon-star&#34; 
      data-size=&#34;large&#34; 
      data-show-count=&#34;true&#34; 
      aria-label=&#34;Star simskij/awesome-software-architecture on GitHub&#34;&gt;
    Star
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;




&lt;div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;
    containrrr/shoutrrr
  &lt;/h3&gt;
  
	&lt;p&gt;
	  Shoutrrr is a notification package for go applications, heavily inspired by the python library  &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/caronc/apprise&#34;&gt;caronc/apprise&lt;/a&gt;. It is also usable as a standalone CLI tool.
  &lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;a class=&#34;github-button&#34;
		 href=&#34;https://github.com/containrrr/shoutrrr&#34; 
      data-icon=&#34;octicon-star&#34; 
      data-size=&#34;large&#34; 
      data-show-count=&#34;true&#34; 
      aria-label=&#34;Star containrrr/shoutrrr on GitHub&#34;&gt;
    Star
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;




&lt;div&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;
    containrrr/watchtower
  &lt;/h3&gt;
  
	&lt;p&gt;
	  Watchtower is currently the most popular solution for automating the updates of base images for  docker containers. The project is written exclusively in Go. Maintained through the Containrrr team.
  &lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;a class=&#34;github-button&#34;
		 href=&#34;https://github.com/containrrr/watchtower&#34; 
      data-icon=&#34;octicon-star&#34; 
      data-size=&#34;large&#34; 
      data-show-count=&#34;true&#34; 
      aria-label=&#34;Star containrrr/watchtower on GitHub&#34;&gt;
    Star
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;





&lt;hr/&gt;

&lt;a class=&#34;github-button&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/simskij&#34; data-size=&#34;large&#34; data-show-count=&#34;true&#34; aria-label=&#34;Follow @simskij on GitHub&#34;&gt;
    Follow @simskij
&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class=&#34;github-button&#34; 
    href=&#34;https://github.com/sponsors/simskij&#34;
    data-icon=&#34;octicon-heart&#34;
    data-size=&#34;large&#34;
    aria-label=&#34;Sponsor @simskij on GitHub&#34;&gt;
    Sponsor
&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
